[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Written evidence from Forum of Insurance Lawyers (FOIL) (MI0016)
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]FOIL[bold] (The Forum of Insurance Lawyers) exists to provide a forum for communication and the exchange of information between lawyers acting predominantly or exclusively for insurance clients (except legal expenses insurers) within firms of solicitors, as barriste
[normal]rs, or as in-house lawyers for insurers or self-insurers. FOIL is an active lobbying organisation on matters concerning insurance litigation. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]FOIL[bold] represents over 8
[normal]000 members. It is the only organisation which represents solicitors who act for defendant
[normal]s in civil proceedings.
